          "validation_ok": true,
          "errors": [],
          "repaired": false,
          "latency_ms": 11359,
          "unit_kind": "paragraph"
        },
        "text": "Require platforms to unbundle features As soon as a user opens a platform, they are confronted with a variety of features: from photo- and video streams to messages, stories, shopping and more. It is often not possible to use just one feature a platform offers and ignore the rest. Platforms also promote certain (more lucrative and addictive) features, for instance by featuring them on the home screen, or by inserting them into other features (such as including previews of video's into a photo feed). Users have too little control over how and for what purpose they use the platform. Bits of Freedom advises the European Commission to take the following measures.",
        "chunk_meta": {
          "section_id": "s8",
          "section_path": [
            "A. Attracting attention",
            "4. Give users more control over sorting algorithms"
